    {
      "title": {
        "de": "Der kürzeste Weg beim Wechsel",
        "en": "The shortest path when changing"
      },
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": {
            "de": "Beim Wechsel zwischen zwei Akkorden gilt: Lass gemeinsame Töne liegen und bewege so wenige Finger wie möglich. Wähle dazu immer die Umkehrung des Zielakkords, bei der die gemeinsamen Töne an Ort und Stelle bleiben.",
            "en": "When changing between two chords: leave common notes in place and move as few fingers as possible. To do that, always choose the inversion of the target chord where the common notes stay put."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "sub",
          "title": {
            "de": "Die Merkregel",
            "en": "The rule"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "head": [
            {
              "de": "Abstand der Stufen",
              "en": "Number distance"
            },
            {
              "de": "Beispiele",
              "en": "Examples"
            },
            {
              "de": "bleiben",
              "en": "stay"
            },
            {
              "de": "Finger bewegen",
              "en": "fingers move"
            }
          ],
          "rows": [
            [
              {
                "de": "Terz oder Sexte",
                "en": "Third or sixth"
              },
              {
                "de": "1↔3, 1↔6, 2↔4, 4↔6",
                "en": "1↔3, 1↔6, 2↔4, 4↔6"
              },
              {
                "de": "2 Töne",
                "en": "2 notes"
              },
              {
                "de": "nur 1",
                "en": "only 1"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "de": "Quarte oder Quinte",
                "en": "Fourth or fifth"
              },
              {
                "de": "1↔4, 1↔5, 2↔5",
                "en": "1↔4, 1↔5, 2↔5"
              },
              {
                "de": "1 Ton",
                "en": "1 note"
              },
              {
                "de": "2",
                "en": "2"
              }
            ],
            [
              {
                "de": "Schritt (nebeneinander)",
                "en": "Step (adjacent)"
              },
              {
                "de": "1↔2, 4↔5, 5↔6",
                "en": "1↔2, 4↔5, 5↔6"
              },
              {
                "de": "0",
                "en": "0"
              },
              {
                "de": "alle 3 (ganze Hand)",
                "en": "all 3 (whole hand)"
              }
            ]
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "note",
          "text": {
            "de": "Merksatz: Terz/Sexte → 2 Töne bleiben, 1 Finger bewegt sich. Quarte/Quinte → 1 Ton bleibt, 2 Finger. Direkt nebeneinander → kein Ton bleibt, die ganze Hand rutscht (meist einen Schritt).",
            "en": "Remember: third/sixth → 2 notes stay, 1 finger moves. Fourth/fifth → 1 note stays, 2 fingers. Directly adjacent → no note stays, the whole hand slides (usually one step)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
